HEADWORD: Ovicell
<hw>O"vi*cell`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Ovum</ets> +
<ets>cell</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the dilatations
of the body wall of Bryozoa in which the ova sometimes undergo the first
stages of their development. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Chilostoma</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ovicular</ent>⟦br⟧
